defs.docs:
This crate is a Rust library for using the [Serde] serialization framework
 with data in [YAML] file format.

defs.name: from_str
defs.docs: Deserialize an instance of type `T` from a string of YAML text.

defs.name: from_reader
defs.docs: Deserialize an instance of type `T` from an IO stream of YAML.

defs.name: from_slice
defs.docs: Deserialize an instance of type `T` from bytes of YAML text.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs:
This type represents all possible errors that can occur when serializing or
 deserializing YAML data.

defs.name: Result
defs.docs: Alias for a `Result` with the error type `serde_yaml::Error`.

defs.name: Location
defs.docs: This type represents the location that an error occured.

defs.name: index
defs.docs: The byte index of the error

defs.name: line
defs.docs: The line of the error

defs.name: column
defs.docs: The column of the error

defs.name: location
defs.docs: Returns the Location from the error if one exists.

defs.name: Mapping
defs.docs: A YAML mapping in which the keys and values are both `serde_yaml::Value`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates an empty YAML map.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs: Creates an empty YAML map with the given initial capacity.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more elements to be inserted
 into the map. The map may reserve more space to avoid frequent
 allocations.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity of the map as much as possible. It will drop down
 as much as possible while maintaining the internal rules and possibly
 leaving some space in accordance with the resize policy.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, k: Value, v: Value) -> Option<Value>
defs.docs:
Inserts a key-value pair into the map. If the key already existed, the
 old value is returned.

defs.name: contains_key
defs.docs: Checks if the map contains the given key.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns the value corresponding to the key in the map.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Returns the mutable reference corresponding to the key in the map.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes and returns the value corresponding to the key from the map.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs:
Returns the maximum number of key-value pairs the map can hold without
 reallocating.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of key-value pairs in the map.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns whether the map is currently empty.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the map of all key-value pairs.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs:
Returns a double-ended iterator visiting all key-value pairs in order of
 insertion. Iterator element type is `(&'a Value, &'a Value)`.

defs.name: iter_mut
defs.docs:
Returns a double-ended iterator visiting all key-value pairs in order of
 insertion. Iterator element type is `(&'a Value, &'a mut ValuE)`.

defs.name: Number
defs.docs: Represents a YAML number, whether integer or floating point.

defs.name: is_i64
defs.docs:
Returns true if the `Number` is an integer between `i64::MIN` and
 `i64::MAX`.

defs.name: is_u64
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Number` is an integer between zero and `u64::MAX`.

defs.name: is_f64
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Number` can be represented by f64.

defs.name: as_i64
defs.docs:
If the `Number` is an integer, represent it as i64 if possible. Returns
 None otherwise.

defs.name: as_u64
defs.docs:
If the `Number` is an integer, represent it as u64 if possible. Returns
 None otherwise.

defs.name: as_f64
defs.docs: Represents the number as f64 if possible. Returns None otherwise.

defs.name: is_nan
defs.docs: Returns true if this value is NaN and false otherwise.

defs.name: is_infinite
defs.docs:
Returns true if this value is positive infinity or negative infinity and
 false otherwise.

defs.name: is_finite
defs.docs: Returns true if this number is neither infinite nor NaN.

defs.name: to_writer
defs.docs: Serialize the given data structure as YAML into the IO stream.

defs.name: to_vec
defs.docs: Serialize the given data structure as a YAML byte vector.

defs.name: to_string
defs.docs: Serialize the given data structure as a String of YAML.

defs.name: Null
defs.docs: Represents a YAML null value.

defs.name: Bool
defs.docs: Represents a YAML boolean.

defs.name: Number
defs.docs: Represents a YAML numerical value, whether integer or floating point.

defs.name: String
defs.docs: Represents a YAML string.

defs.name: Sequence
defs.docs:
Represents a YAML sequence in which the elements are
 `serde_yaml::Value`.

defs.name: Mapping
defs.docs:
Represents a YAML mapping in which the keys and values are both
 `serde_yaml::Value`.

defs.name: Value
defs.value: Value::{Null, Bool, Number, String, Sequence, Mapping}
defs.docs: Represents any valid YAML value.

defs.name: Sequence
defs.docs: A YAML sequence in which the elements are `serde_yaml::Value`.

defs.name: to_value
defs.docs:
Convert a `T` into `serde_yaml::Value` which is an enum that can represent
 any valid YAML data.

defs.name: from_value
defs.docs: Interpret a `serde_yaml::Value` as an instance of type `T`.

defs.name: get
defs.docs:
Index into a YAML sequence or map. A string index can be used to access
 a value in a map, and a usize index can be used to access an element of
 an sequence.

defs.name: is_null
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Value` is a Null. Returns false otherwise.

defs.name: as_null
defs.docs: If the `Value` is a Null, returns (). Returns None otherwise.

defs.name: is_bool
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Value` is a Boolean. Returns false otherwise.

defs.name: as_bool
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is a Boolean, returns the associated bool. Returns None
 otherwise.

defs.name: is_number
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Value` is a Number. Returns false otherwise.

defs.name: is_i64
defs.docs:
Returns true if the `Value` is an integer between `i64::MIN` and
 `i64::MAX`.

defs.name: as_i64
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is an integer, represent it as i64 if possible. Returns
 None otherwise.

defs.name: is_u64
defs.docs:
Returns true if the `Value` is an integer between `u64::MIN` and
 `u64::MAX`.

defs.name: as_u64
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is an integer, represent it as u64 if possible. Returns
 None otherwise.

defs.name: is_f64
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Value` is a number that can be represented by f64.

defs.name: as_f64
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is a number, represent it as f64 if possible. Returns
 None otherwise.

defs.name: is_string
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Value` is a String. Returns false otherwise.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is a String, returns the associated str. Returns None
 otherwise.

defs.name: is_sequence
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Value` is a sequence. Returns false otherwise.

defs.name: as_sequence
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is a sequence, return a reference to it if possible.
 Returns None otherwise.

defs.name: as_sequence_mut
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is a sequence, return a mutable reference to it if
 possible. Returns None otherwise.

defs.name: is_mapping
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Value` is a mapping. Returns false otherwise.

defs.name: as_mapping
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is a mapping, return a reference to it if possible.
 Returns None otherwise.

defs.name: as_mapping_mut
defs.docs:
If the `Value` is a mapping, return a reference to it if possible.
 Returns None otherwise.

defs.name: Index
defs.docs:
A type that can be used to index into a `serde_yaml::Value`. See the `get`
 and `get_mut` methods of `Value`.

defs.name: index_into
defs.docs: Return None if the key is not already in the sequence or object.

defs.name: index_into_mut
defs.value: fn <'v> (&self, v: &'v mut Value) -> Option<&'v mut Value>
defs.docs: Return None if the key is not already in the sequence or object.

defs.name: index_or_insert
defs.value: fn <'v> (&self, v: &'v mut Value) -> &'v mut Value
defs.docs:
Panic if sequence index out of bounds. If key is not already in the object,
 insert it with a value of null. Panic if Value is a type that cannot be
 indexed into, except if Value is null then it can be treated as an empty
 object.
